    "privileged_info_summary": "The task requests lookup of five real chemicals on CAMEO Chemicals (https://cameochemicals.noaa.gov), a NOAA hazardous chemical database. The five chemicals—Bromine, Potassium Permanganate, Hydrazine, Carbon Disulfide, and Titanium Tetrachloride—are real compounds with verified physical properties from CAMEO datasheets. Bromine is a dark reddish-brown liquid with pungent odor; boiling point 139.2°F (59.6°C), melting point 19°F (-7.2°C). Potassium permanganate is a purple crystalline solid that decomposes rather than boils; melting point above 464°F (240°C). Hydrazine is a colorless liquid with ammonia-like odor; boiling point 236.3°F (113.5°C), melting point 36°F (2.2°C). Carbon disulfide is a colorless-to-yellow volatile liquid with strong odor; boiling point 116°F (46.5°C), melting point -167°F (-111.5°C). Titanium tetrachloride is a colorless fuming liquid with pungent odor; boiling point 277.5°F (136.4°C), melting point -11.4°F (-24.1°C). Metadata values show minor differences from authoritative sources, likely due to rounding conventions and significant figures.",
